## Agent Commands

> Vault maintenance commands you can run during sessions.

| When | Command | Purpose |
|------|---------|---------|
| Start of session | `agentfs selfcheck --quick` | Verify vault health |
| After learning new fact | `agentfs memory add semantic --json '{"type":"FACT","content":"..."}'` | Persist knowledge |
| After editing manifest | `agentfs compile` | Recompile native configs |
| Something feels wrong | `agentfs doctor --fix` | Auto-diagnose and repair |
| Vault setup needed | `agentfs onboard --full` | Full guided vault setup |
| End of session | `agentfs status --json` | Log final state |

### Safety rules
- NEVER run `agentfs clean --all` without explicit user instruction
- NEVER delete memory files directly — use `agentfs memory` commands
- NEVER edit compiled outputs (CLAUDE.md, .cursor/rules/) — edit manifest, then compile
- All agent-initiated changes are logged to `.agentos/proc/agent-actions.log`
